  "topic_name": "Area and Perimeter of Plane Figures",
  "canonical_explanation": {
    "text": "This topic covers the measurement of area and perimeter for various plane figures including circles, sectors, segments, triangles, trapeziums, and composite figures. Key formulas include: Circle circumference C = 2πr and area A = πr²; Arc length = (θ/360°) × 2πr; Sector area = (θ/360°) × πr²; Segment area = Sector area - Triangle area; Triangle area using Heron's formula A = √[s(s-a)(s-b)(s-c)] where s is semi-perimeter; Trapezium area A = ½(a+b)h where a and b are parallel sides and h is height.",
    "rules": [
      "Always use consistent units throughout calculations",
      "When using π, specify whether to use 22/7, 3.14, or keep answer in terms of π",
      "For composite figures, identify and calculate individual components before combining",
      "In Heron's formula, calculate semi-perimeter s = (a+b+c)/2 first",
      "For segments, remember to subtract the triangular portion from the sector",
      "Arc length and sector area both use the ratio of angle to 360°"
    ]
  },
